                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 3, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Please confirm Press Reports that the Minister for Foreign Affairs has
                    ordered Insull to leave Greece. Unless a definite date has been set for
                    expulsion you should make inquiry of the Foreign Minister <pb facs="0669"
                        n="569" xml:id="pg_569"/> as to when he intends to give effect to the
                    assurances given to you especially that of February 16, and state that you are
                    doing so under instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
